oc:kn_4fa9ee26 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Global event listener hooks used by many component instances" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Without deduplication, listener count scales O(N) with component instances. With useSWRSubscription, it stays O(1) — one listener regardless of N." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is especially impactful for frequently-fired events like keydown, scroll, or resize where each listener adds per-event overhead." .

oc:kn_a7ae275a a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When multiple components need to react to the same global event source" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use useSWRSubscription from SWR to ensure only one global listener exists regardless of how many component instances subscribe to the same key." ;
    oc:hasRationale "useSWRSubscription deduplicates the subscription under the hood — the subscribe function runs once per unique SWR key, not once per consumer." .

oc:kn_be94904f a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using hooks that attach to global event sources like window, document, or WebSocket" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never register separate global event listeners (e.g., window.addEventListener) inside each component instance via useEffect — N mounted instances create N duplicate listeners." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each duplicate listener wastes memory and CPU cycles processing the same event independently, degrading performance at scale." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d9def5db a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing shared event listener hooks that accept per-instance callbacks" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "tsx" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Maintain a module-level Map<string, Set<() => void>> to track registered callbacks per event key, registering/unregistering in useEffect while the actual DOM listener is managed exclusively inside useSWRSubscription." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Separating callback registration (per-instance) from the DOM listener (singleton) allows N consumers to share 1 listener while preserving individual callbacks." .

oc:kn_fb719b99 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Code review and performance optimization of React components" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Any useEffect that calls window.addEventListener or document.addEventListener with the same event type should be audited for deduplication via useSWRSubscription." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Duplicate global listeners are a silent performance tax — they don't cause bugs but waste resources proportionally to component instance count." .

